name: What So Not
description: '''What So Not''' is an electronic music project by Australian DJ and record producer '''Emoh Instead''' (stage name of '''Christopher John Emerson'''). What So Not has toured the world, playing in various festivals, including [[Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival]], [[Pukkelpop]], [[Ultra Music Festival]] and [[Lollapalooza]]. What So Not is best known for his hits such as "Innerbloom" (What So Not Remix) (by [[RÜFÜS DU SOL]]), "Gemini" (featuring [[George Maple]]), "Jaguar", "High You Are" and "Tell Me" (with [[RL Grime]]). He has featured on charts such as the [[ARIA Charts|Australian Singles Chart]], [[Triple J Hottest 100]], and USA iTunes Dance Album chart. He released his debut album titled ''[[Not All the Beautiful Things]]'' on 9 March 2018.
